1. B, E, A, D, C
2. E, D, B, A, C
3. The display property is used to specify how the element box should be handled in the layout; for example, as a
block element starting on a new line or as an inline element staying in the text flow.
4. Elements set to display: none are completely removed from the normal flow and the space they would have
occupied is closed up. An element with visibility set to hidden is invisible, but the empty space it would have
occupied in the normal flow is still there.
5. List items can be turned into inline elements using the display property, or floated to one edge so they stack up
next to one another.
6. C, the :hover selector.